#!/usr/bin/pseudocode
This is not yet a runnable script

$ sudo apt-get update; apt-get upgrade
$ sudo apt-get install git
$ cd ~
$ git clone git://github.com/AGNUcius/GNUnix.git

$ mv GNUnix/* .
$ mv GNUnix/.* .


Basic Desktop:
 wdm alternatives: slim, lightdm
 xterm alternatives: urxvt, aterm
$ sudo apt-get install xinit xterm icewm wdm big-cursor


Manage: Files, Processess, Power, Screen, Audio
$ sudo apt-get install emelfm2 htop pm-utils xlockmore alsamixer

File manager more like Windows Explorer
$ sudo apt-get --no-install-recommends install xfe


Web browser
Alternatives: firefox, iceweasle
$ sudo apt-get install chromium-browser


Extra tools that I use
$ sudo apt-get install emacs p7zip-full dhex


Enable backup to LiveCD
$ mkdir ~/down
$ cd ~/down
$ wget http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/tux2live/Tux2live/Stable/tux2live-v1.2.0-50.tgz
$ tar xzvf tux2live-v1.2.0-50.tgz
$ cd tux2live
$ pkg.install squashfs-tools genisoimage live-boot live-boot-initramfs-tools
$ pkg.cleanup
$ sudo ./tux2live

$ if (laptop)
$ {
$  sudo apt-get install yacpi wicd-curses wireless-regdb crda iw rfkill
$  sudo rfkill list all
$  sudo pm-powersave
$ }


For the first login (if using wdm), select "icewm-session" from the "Start WM" button.


Needed to play audio as non-root
$ sudo add UserName audio


See ../README.txt for more info
